      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If a just society is defined by the protection of all its members, then the argument for universal healthcare becomes a moral imperative rather than a policy debate. Framing it as a \"government takeover\" when the alternative is allowing preventable deaths certainly prioritizes profit over human life. In this view, the supposed \"inefficiency\" of public systems is a far smaller cost than the catastrophic human and economic toll of a two-tiered healthcare system.",
      "source": "target",
